node.text:
Happy #mahimonday y’all 
had such a great weekend fishing the @battlegroundbahamas #tournament with team @pelagicgear @reelgals @tyler_kuehl @audreydelligatti @reeldread242 @jeremyhersom @winterlove242 .. it was a very tough/slow couple of days fishing for everyone but we managed to pull through with a couple sizable fish 🥰 so proud of our team👏 I caught this pretty boy on day one towards the end of the day🙌 let me know if you want to hear the story behind it in the comments😁 … Huge thank you to @visitgbi  for inviting us to stay at @tainobeachresort and visit they’re beautiful island #grandbahama during the Tournament!!💙 I also want to give a huge thank you to @anythingmarine for lending us your boat after we came across a couple hiccups in our plans, you saved the trip!🙌….. 
we went through a crazy storm on our way to the #Bahamas , between my phone not taking a charge from being drenched and not having any service I didn’t get a chance to post videos throughout the trip to keep you updated but I will be posting videos and pictures of the trip In in my stories soon!🥰…
#pelagicgear #pelagicgirl #pelagicworldwide #thebahamas #visitthebahamas #visitgbi 
.

node.text:
if you’re feeling the #mondayblues , I’m here to give you hogs and kisses🐷😘…
This is the one that got away, let’s just say I need a lot more practice with the pole spear; especially going deeper than I’m used to. as I was going down I started to lose grip and only nicked this guy in the tail, then lost him. @t.furey AKA “Big Daddy Hot-hands”😂 had been driving the boat all day while we were diving and decided to get in. BOOM! he #gotem .. we didn’t know it was the same fish until @thinktankg pointed it out 😍…. it’s been at least three years since I’ve gone diving (I don’t think lobstering counts) so I was only expecting to make it to 20 feet if I was lucky, wellllllll; i’m very proud to say that I dove 47 feet that day😍 and I am motivated to start driving again🥰 we’ll see what the future holds for me. I can’t thank @thinktankg @grooper and @t.furey enough for how informative and patient you guys were with us. I LEARNED SO SO MUCH!!! and will be forever grateful! I had such a magical weekend with you guys and @coley_jens @marialuvsme4 🥰 ILY!!!🥰……
i’m rocking the newest pattern Blue dorado( which I’m obsessed with😍🤩) by @pelagicgear @pelagicgirl 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥

node.text:
What a magical weekend!!!!
On day one, late afternoon a few big mahi showed up and we got them to the boat. @coley_jens caught her personal best😍🙌!!! that thing was huge! … As @marialuvsme4 was fighting hers, The mahi bite quickly turned into the most insane tuna frenzy I’ve ever seen in my life! on more than one occasion every line that was in the water was hooked up, organized chaos at its finest. Everyone knew what to do, when they started pin willing, we all followed our fish, Over under - over under; we had a few tangles, but were able to get out of it. Not a single fish was chafed off 🤯 as soon as a fish was gaffed, A bait was ready to go for the next fight.  blood literally everywhere!!! in that crazy moment I was able to catch two #yellowfin and five #blackfin One of the black-fin was the biggest I’ve ever seen…… mannnnn I can literally write a book if I typed erything from this past weekend😇 This was just a fraction of this incredible trip……..
if you’ve made it this far I have to tell you how obsessed I am with The newest Dorado line by @pelagicgear @pelagicgirl every time they come out with a new look it just keeps getting better🤩 The style, The color, the sizing, the print, the Comfort!!! ALLL of it on point!!😎
